pr_review_body:
@samuelcolvin, please beware that this PR introduces breaking changes

This was previously a valid usecase, but with these changes it will raise an error because :
```py
def test_custom_getter_dict():
    class TestCls:
        x = 1
        y = 2

    def custom_getter_dict(obj):
        assert isinstance(obj, TestCls)
        return {'x': 42, 'y': 24}

    class Model(BaseModel):
        x: int
        y: int
        class Config:
            orm_mode = True
            getter_dict = custom_getter_dict
    model = Model.from_orm(TestCls())
    assert model.dict() == {'x': 42, 'y': 24}
```

@architkulkarni this is looking way better. I'm a little disconcerted that we have to do the string parsing in C++, but it may be ok.

Is it possible that we just make this a more structured format in the protobuf instead of just a list of strings? We could have the protobuf be:

```
message InternalURI {
  string protocol = 1;
  string uri = 2;
}
```

Then the GCS could just look at protocol and we could avoid the whole parsing thing. Would that work? Sorry for not thinking of it sooner, it might be a cleaner way to do this... if this is a big change I'm ok with the status quo

Note that the PR would have been really smaller with something like:
```
class Server:
    def __init__(self):
        try:
            self.initialize()
        except Exception:
            logger.exception("Initialization error")

    def initialize(self):
        ...
```

@BaritoneBeard, thanks for the PRs from you and your teammates :smile:. 

I've added in my review, though I'd encourage you all to wait maybe a day or two more before taking action on it, so that others on the dev team can chime in.

Can I ask, how are you all (@Sousa8697 @MollyCroke and @ericclessantostv and yourself) related professionally? Just curious if this PR you all submitted together is part of a class project or team project of some kind?

@alexjarosch thanks for this! The paper seems to be highly used so a priori I think this is a good addition to the library. The implementation is beautifully simple, too! I'd love to hear from other @scikit-image/core devs with more deconv experience (more than ~0 😂) what they think.

We're busy preparing our next release so I haven't done a complete review with reference to the papers, but I've done a first pass with some minor suggestions, as well as a link that I hope will get you unstuck with regards to the reference data. 

Thanks again and I'm looking forward to the next pass!

@tned73 Thank you for your contribution! Looks good to me! This change makes the `MoneyField` more in line with the default behavior of other Django fields (they have `default=NOT_PROVIDED`

I will add minor changes in subsequent commits (reduce branching & changelog entry).

As for `mixer` - in the future, I'd like to use the Hypothesis' [Django plugin](https://hypothesis.readthedocs.io/en/latest/django.html) for data generation, but I'll compare them first (they may be not mutually exclusive).
